  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per 10 minutes</p>\n<hr />\n<p>When you focus your magic on an ally, you can remove harmful conditions.</p>\n<p>If your next action is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} from a spell slot, and that spell targets only a single ally, you can also attempt to remove a harmful condition from that ally. The condition must be one that could be removed by your Mercy feat, including those granted by later feats such as @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.kZdcoaTD849QalR9]{Greater Mercy}.</p>\n<p>Attempt a counteract check based on the spell's DC and level. This effect is in addition to the normal effects of your spell.</p>"
